<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> hold a rein on something • hold the reins of something</xh5><p> <i>hold a rein on something—</i>check or restrain smth., such as one’s emotions: Age and experience managed to <u>hold a rein on</u> the terror that wanted to overcome her.</p><p> <i>hold the reins of something—</i>exercise control over smth.: Most were fierce military men and none could <u>hold the reins of</u> power without the support of the army.</p> </entry>
